rison that occur within the gendered context of substandard prison conditions, inequalities of capital among those imprisoned, and relationships with correctional staff. In Search of Safety proposes a way forward—the implementation of international human-rights standards for U.S. prisons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aPrisonsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aWomen prisonersxViolence againstzUnited States. 0aWomen prisonerszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aamerican womens prisons.  aconflict in womens prisons.  afemale inmates.  afemale prisoners.  agendered harm.  agendered violence.  ahuman rights violations in prison.  ahuman rights.  alife in womens prison.  aphysical safety in womens prisons.  aprison capital.  aprison conditions.  aprison conflict.  aprison life.  aprison persona.  aprison violence.  aprisoners rights.  aviolence in womens prisons.  awomens pathway to prison.  awomens prisons in the us.  awomens prisons.1 aPollock, Joycelyn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWells, James, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z97831106385160 cprintz978052028872040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520963566?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963566423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520963566/original  a978-3-11-063851-6  Urban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019c2016d2019  a978-3-11-0667